  "prompt": "What is the essay asked in civil service main exam in 2002?",
  "response": "In the 2002 Civil Service Main Examination conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) in India, candidates were given a choice of topics to write an essay on. The essay topics provided in the 2002 exam were as follows:\n\n1. **Modern technological education and human values**\n2. **Search for sources of Energy**\n3. **Ethical Dilemmas of Modern Science**\n4. **India's Role in Promoting ASEAN Co-operation**\n5. **The Masks of New Imperialism**\n6. **The amorphous nature of Indian polity**\n7. **Need for a New Paradigm of Development**\n8. **Whither Indian Democracy?**\n9. **Relevance of Socialism in Today's World**\n10. **The Emerging Global Order, Political and Economic**\n\nCandidates were required to select one topic and write an essay of around 2500-3000 words. The essay paper is part of the mains examination and is designed to test the candidate's ability to express coherent and well-structured ideas on a subject of general interest.",
